function onLoad()
  --- Tutorial Stuff ---
  object1 = getObjectFromGUID(object1_GUID)

  stop_checker = getObjectFromGUID(stop_checker_GUID)

  object1.setName('Object1')
  object2.setName('Object2')
  draw_checker.setName('That Stupid Checker')  -- s a d
  stop_checker.setName('That Other Stupid Checker')
  deck.setName('Deck')

  stop_checker.createButton(button2_parameters)

function deal_me(objectButtonClicked, playerColorClicked)
  -- when clicked, it'll deal the player who pressed the button 1 card
  caller_color = playerColorClicked
  printToAll(playerColorClicked.." player hits")
  deck.deal(1, caller_color)

  -- might be a good place to get value of said dealt card and add to
  -- the player's counter. if counter > 21, then it's a bust :o
end

function kill_me(objectButtonClicked, playerColorClicked)
  -- when clicked, the game stops
  caller_color = playerColorClicked
  printToAll(playerColorClicked.." player stands")

  -- this is probably where we compare the counters of dealer and player
  -- to decide who wins uwu
end
